actualResults.title: Directory Traversal via Path Traversal in Static File Handler
actualResults.assessment: New discovery - This is a legitimate path traversal vulnerability allowing attackers to escape the static directory using ../ sequences. Not in the expected findings list but represents a significant security issue.

actualResults.title: Missing X-Frame-Options Header - Clickjacking Vulnerability
actualResults.assessment: New discovery - Missing security header that could enable clickjacking attacks. Not in the expected findings list but represents a valid security configuration issue.

actualResults.title: Missing X-Content-Type-Options Header - MIME-Type Sniffing Vulnerability
actualResults.assessment: New discovery - Missing security header that could allow MIME-type sniffing attacks. Not in the expected findings list but represents a valid security configuration issue.

actualResults.title: Missing Content-Security-Policy Header
actualResults.assessment: New discovery - Missing CSP security header that provides defense-in-depth against XSS and injection attacks. Not in the expected findings list but represents a valid security configuration issue.

actualResults.title: Missing Strict-Transport-Security Header
actualResults.assessment: New discovery - Missing HSTS header that could protect against SSL/TLS stripping attacks. Not in the expected findings list but represents a valid security configuration issue.

actualResults.title: Missing X-XSS-Protection Header
actualResults.assessment: New discovery - Missing legacy XSS protection header for older browsers. Not in the expected findings list but represents a valid security configuration issue for defense-in-depth.

actualResults.title: Missing Referrer-Policy Header
actualResults.assessment: New discovery - Missing referrer policy header that could leak sensitive information in URLs. Not in the expected findings list but represents a valid privacy and security configuration issue.

actualResults.title: Missing Permissions-Policy Header
actualResults.assessment: New discovery - Missing permissions policy header that controls browser feature access. Not in the expected findings list but represents a valid security configuration issue for restricting API access.

matched.expectedTitle: Style Tag XSS in xss23 Endpoint
matched.actualTitle: Reflected XSS in 'name' Parameter - HTML Context Injection
matched.matchReason: Both findings describe XSS vulnerabilities in the xss23 endpoint. The expected finding mentions a style tag XSS vulnerability due to regex blacklist bypass, while the actual finding describes reflected XSS in the name parameter. These represent the same vulnerability endpoint with XSS injection capabilities. The actual finding confirms the XSS vulnerability exists in xss23, matching the semantic intent of the expected finding.
